dHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB71bf9bc9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">their stake could be wor=
th</a>=C2=A0about $165 million. But the deal is still in limbo, due mostly =
to the US Securities and Exchange Commission=E2=80=99s review of the proxy =
statement for the merger,=C2=A0and the sponsors had to put up another $2.9 =
million for a three-month extension, and they waited until the absolute las=
t minute to do that. On the one hand betting $2.9 million to win $165 milli=
on seems like a good deal. On the other hand the odds aren=E2=80=99t great,=
 money might be a bit tight, and every penny comes out of the sponsors=E2=
=80=99 own pockets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/29111652.284535/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvNDlhY=
